If it isn't working it might be because there are a few different versions of that dll with the same name (out on the net), I had that problem once.

@morp3d-

Blocking the program in firewall keeps it from "calling home" and finding out that it's not a legal copy.  This will also prevent online play, but usually you can't do that anyway with these cracked copies.   (borderlands 1 was a rare exception).

Telling your antivirus that buddha.dll is a safe file keeps your antivirus from blocking the file from running  (Almost all anti-virus companies label _every single_ bit of cracked software as a virus, usually a malicious one!, even if they aren't malicious at all.  It's kind of a collusion with software producers to scare everyone away from cracked software).

